description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title – CYPS Public Health Nursing: Senior Administrator – Band 3&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Base – Stonebury (Lydney)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary – £19,737 to £21,142 per annum pro rata&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours per week – Min 22.5 – Max 30 hrs (3 or 4 days) 08:30 – 16:30 or 09:00 – 17:00pm.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen within the Gloucester Public Health Nurse team, for a Senior Administrator.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a reliable, well organised and highly motivated individual to provide a comprehensive administration service within the Health Visiting and School Nursing 0 -19 Service of Gloucestershire Health and Care NHS Foundation Trust. You will need to be conscientious, with the ability to work under pressure, plan and coordinate a demanding workload in order to meet strict deadlines. The nature of the work requires accuracy, sensitivity and confidentiality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent communication skills are essential as is the ability to liaise with senior managers, clinical team members and people at all levels. The successful applicant should have robust computer skills and have the ability to learn new skills and processes. An ability to handle sensitive and confidential information in a professional manner at all times will be necessary. You will also be able to work on your own initiative and as part of a team with a positive and solution-focused attitude.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should be able to demonstrate administrative experience including excellent IT skills including using Microsoft Outlook, Word and Excel. Experience of using Systm1 database is preferred but training will be given.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An ability to prioritise effectively and use initiative is essential. It is important that the successful applicant is able to adapt to change and has an excellent telephone manner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you think that you meet the person specification and can work the hours as stated above, then we want to hear from you. Please note, only candidates who meet all of the essential elements specified in the person specification will be considered for interview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information or to arrange an informal visit please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bev Harvey - Health Visiting Team Leader, on 07747008253&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The qualification, training &amp; experience requirements for the role are underlined in the Job Description/Person Specification.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 8th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: 18th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post requires the post holder to be able to undertake all statutory and mandatory training and post holders must be able to undertake physical interventions. Fitness for physical intervention will be assessed by Occupational Health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A valid UK driving licence plus the use of own transport for business purposes is essential. For qualifying staff the Trust has a Lease Car Scheme in place and also offers a popular Salary Sacrifice Car Scheme with our partner Tusker.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To ensure you fully understand how the Trust, as a Data Controller, will process and store your data please read the attached document ‘ Applicant and Staff Privacy Notice’ prior to applying for the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates for any staff appointment shall, when making application, disclose in writing to the Trust whether they are related to any governor. Failure to disclose such a relationship may disqualify a candidate and, if appointed, may render him/her liable to dismissal.&lt;/p&gt;
